==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sulphamic
<hw>Sulph*am"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to a sulphamide; derived from, or related to, a
sulphamide; specifically, designating an amido acid derivative,
<chform>NH2.SO2.OH</chform>, of sulphuric acid (analogous to sulphonic
acid) which is not known in the free state, but is known in its
salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphamide</ent>⟦br⟧
